{"actor":{"id":"claude-opus-4-8","type":"agent"},"content":{"blocks":[{"caller":{"type":"direct"},"id":"toolu_01P221LpDXAeVYFQoHutgsPQ","input":{"command":"git add -A && git commit -q -F - <<'EOF'\nRe-normalize preserved unrecognized events (0.6.0)\n\n`cledger renormalize` (library `renormalize()`) turns each preserved\n`unrecognized` event this version can now interpret into the proper\n`conversation_turn`, appending a `supersession` event linking the two so\nconsumers see the interpreted turn instead of the raw placeholder. This is\nthe supersession half of the format-drift roadmap item; preservation shipped\nin 0.5.0.\n\nId fidelity is the crux: each adapter exposes `renormalizeUnrecognized`,\nwhich re-feeds the stored `raw.data` through the same `convertLine` the live\ncapture loop uses, with the identity-determining inputs recovered from the\npreserved event (seq, session id, and — for a timestampless codex line —\noccurred_at as the baseTime fallback). The turn therefore gets the exact id a\nlive capture would produce, so a later live capture dedups rather than\nduplicating.\n\nAppend-only and idempotent: the unrecognized event is never deleted, only\nsuperseded; re-runs skip already-superseded targets and dedup on\ndeterministic ids. The reconstructed turn rides the normal appendEvents\nredaction path (idempotent on already-redacted raw.data), and codex\n`reasoning` can never reach this path, so nothing is re-exposed or\nreconstructed. Manual-only for now; auto-triggering on a version bump is a\ndeferred follow-up.\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 <noreply@anthropic.com>\nEOF\ngit log --oneline -1"},"name":"Bash","type":"tool_use"}],"role":"assistant"},"context":{"branch":"main","cwd":"/Users/evintunador/repos/evintunador/conversation-ledger","head":"6526090feef56b39f756077ad43d4692f53a3ccf","repo":"git@github.com:evintunador/conversation-ledger.git"},"conversation":{"id":"claude-code:b9cb2f57-c42d-4fba-a3e5-4675b5c53898","seq":173},"id":"ev1-fb53e4a4d7ed68