ucted.\n- *Routing by `producer.source`* to the owning adapter.\n\n**Tests** (`src/test/renormalize.test.ts`): the blind→renormalize→seeing-capture dedup test for **both** adapters (asserts one turn, not two, plus the supersession link), a skip test for still-unrecognized lines, and a second-run no-op assertion. `npm test`: **102 pass, 0 fail** (1 pre-existing skip).\n\n**Docs**: README roadmap bullet and `docs/WIP_TECHNICAL_DESIGN.md` updated to describe what shipped; auto-triggering on capture is explicitly deferred as a follow-up (per your manual-only choice). `package.json` bumped 0.5.0 → 0.6.0.\n\nOne thing worth flagging for your judgment: I made the `supersession` event's `content` carry `{superseded, by, reason:\"renormalized\", raw_format}` and its `occurred_at` equal to the turn's — both deliberately deterministic so the supersession id is stable across re-runs. If you'd prefer a leaner `content` (say, just `reason`), that's a trivial change, but note that dropping `by`/`superseded` from `content` doesn't lose the link (it lives in `links`), it only makes the event less self-describing when read without following the target.","type":"text"}],"role":"assistant"},"context":{"branch":"main","cwd":"/Users/evintunador/repos/evintunador/conversation-ledger","head":"6526090feef56b39f756077ad43d4692f53a3ccf","repo":"git@github.com:evintunador/conversation-ledger.git"},"conversation":{"id":"claude-code:b9cb2f57-c42d-4fba-a3e5-4675b5c53898","seq":160},"id":"ev1-1ba699963cc4b51462736be1206e80ff8dcbd0678c5b69dd37050c26b5db53f8","kind":"conversation_turn","occurred_at":"2026-07-20T17:05:49.541Z","producer":{"session_id":"b9cb2f57-c42d-4fba-a3e5-4675b5c53898","source":"claude-code","tool":"cledger","version":"0.6.0"},"raw":{"data":{"cwd":"/Users/evintunador/repos/evintunador/conversation-ledger","effort":"high","entrypoint":"cli","gitBranch":"main","isSidechain":false,"message":{"content":[{"text":"Done. The re-normalization half of the format-drift roadmap item is impl